Create a Recipe with Data Prep Classic

Use a Data Prep Classic recipe to transform data before loading it into a dataset. Only Government Cloud users can create recipes with Data Prep Classic.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create a recipe: Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes

In CRM Analytics, click the gear icon () and then click Data Manager to open the data manager.
The data manager opens in a new browser tab.
In the data manager, click the Dataflows & Recipes tab.
Click Create Recipe.
From the list of datasets, select the one that contains the data you want to prepare. Alternatively, you can click the Connected Data tab to select a connected object if your org has Data Sync enabled.

You are prompted to enter a name for the recipe.
Enter a recipe name and then click Next.
The recipe page opens, displaying a preview of the data from your selected dataset or connected object.
title: Creating Recipes with Data Prep Classic
